PID Control Project¶

I have done my project using manual tuning. However, the base algorithm is the same as presented in the lessons.

Affect of P, I, D component of the PID algorithm in their implementation¶

Increase in P component leads to decrease in the rise time however the car overshoots more.
Increase in I component leads to decrease in the rise time however the car overshoots more. Also it takes more time for car to settle.
Increase in D component leads to decrease in the overshoots and few changes are visible in the rise time.

All the can be clearly seen in the examples taken from running the simulator with different values.

Example 1¶

P = 0.3

I = 0.01

D = 2.0
